messages.content: What is the area of a rectangle

The area of a rectangle is calculated using the formula:

$$\text{Area} = \text{length} \times \text{width}$$

Or more concisely:

$$A = l \times w$$

Where:
- $A$ is the area
- $l$ is the length of the rectangle
- $w$ is the width of the rectangle

The area will be expressed in square units (such as square meters, square feet, square inches, etc.), depending on the units used for the length and width measurements.
